2007-11-29 Thomas Kittelmann <Thomas.Kittelmann@cern.ch>

	* Use new sephelper features to place nodes/materials more
	optimally in the scenegraph. Result is significant performance
	improvements everywhere.
	* Represent Trd's that are really just boxes with SoCube's instead
	of SoTrd's. This gives incredible performance improvements for the
	barrel muon chambers. A similar optimisation replacing SoTube's
	with SoCylinders is postponed for now due to problems of
	difference in axis.

